TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,20,1);
$b = random(2,10,1);
$c = random(2,10,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Suppose that \( f(x) = ($a - $b e^{x} )^{$c} \).  Find \(f'(1)\).

$BR $BR

\(f'(1)\) = \{ans_rule(30) \}
$BR

EOT

$ans = $c*($a - $b*exp(1))**($c-1)*(-$b*exp(1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

